It is possible to modify a note with empty body. Content_text field is mandatory and must have a string as data type.

*Precondition:* A note with unique ID exists

*Steps:*

# Send PATCH request to url: {{https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/note/:UniqueID}}

with any existing note’s ID in the params

{noformat}{
}{noformat}

*Expected result:*

(/) PATCH Modify Note data with an empty body does not work. Error message 400 is shown indicating missing required field.

*Actual result:*

(x) PATCH Modify Note data with an empty body works. No errors shown.

It is possible to modify a note with empty field(content_text). The field is mandatory and must have a string as data type.

*Precondition:* A note with unique ID exists

*Steps:*

# Send PATCH request to url: {{https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/note/:UniqueID}}

with any existing note’s ID in the params

{noformat}{
  "content_text": ""
}{noformat}

*Expected result:*

(/) PATCH Modify Note data with an empty mandatory field does not work. Error message 400 is shown indicating missing required field data input.

*Actual result:*

(x) PATCH Modify Note data with an empty mandatory field works. No errors shown.

It is possible to create new note with empty body. Content_text field is mandatory and must have a string as data type.

*Steps:*

# Send POST request to url: {{https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/note}}

{noformat}{
}{noformat}

*Expected result:*

(/) POST Create new Note with an empty body does not work. Error message 400 is shown indicating missing required field.

*Actual result:*

(x) POST Create new Note with an empty body works. No errors shown.

It is possible to create new note with empty field(content_text). The field is mandatory and must have a string as data type.

*Steps:*

# Send POST request to url: {{https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/note}}

{noformat}{
  "content_text": ""
}{noformat}

*Expected result:*

(/) POST Create new Note with an empty mandatory field does not work. Error message 400 is shown indicating missing required field data input.

*Actual result:*

(x) POST Create new Note with an empty mandatory field works. No errors shown.

A new note can be created with data type boolean, even though string is required in documentation.

*Steps:*

# Send POST request to url: {{https://cerebrumhubcrmlite.bubbleapps.io/api/1.1/obj/note}}

{noformat}{
  "content_text": "false"
}{noformat}

*Expected result:*

(/) POST Create new Note with data type boolean does not work. Error message should be shown about invalid data for field content_text.

*Actual result:*

(x) POST Create new Note with data type boolean works. No errors shown.

